    <body>
      <section eId="sec_81">
        <num>81</num>
        <heading>Application of laws; exceptions</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_81__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>every reasonable effort shall be made by the acquiring\nagency to acquire the requisite lands or rights and interests therein by\nnegotiation,</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_81__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>to the greatest extent practicable no person lawfully\noccupying the land shall be required to move from his home, farm or\nbusiness location without at least ninety days written notice from the\nacquiring agency, and</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_81__subsec_c">
          <num>(c)</num>
          <content>
            <p>it will be the policy of the acquiring agency,\nbefore initiating negotiations for the lands, rights and interests\ntherein, to establish the amount which is believed to constitute just\ncompensation under the laws of this state and to make a prompt offer to\nacquire the lands, rights and interests therein for the full amount so\nestablished.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
